defs.docs:
Mutex and RwLock types that do not poison themselves.

 These types expose identical APIs to the standard library `Mutex` and
 `RwLock` except that they do not return `PoisonError`s.

defs.name: Mutex
defs.docs: Like `std::sync::Mutex` except that it does not poison itself.

defs.name: wait
defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&self, guard: MutexGuard<'a, T>) -> MutexGuard<'a, T>

defs.name: wait_timeout
defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&self, guard: MutexGuard<'a, T>, dur: Duration) -> (MutexGuard<'a, T>, WaitTimeoutResult)

defs.name: RwLock
defs.docs: Like `std::sync::RwLock` except that it does not poison itself.
